docs/product-scope.md:5:RunForge is currently a local, deterministic agentic engineering harness. It can run bounded task rails that produce reviewable artifacts instead of directly changing a repository.
docs/product-scope.md:11:- Rails task types for `failure-triage`, `command-check`, `repo-research`, `context-pack`, and `code-proposal`.
docs/product-scope.md:37:- Autonomous delivery without a human decision.
docs/product-scope.md:49:- Broader task rails for more engineering workflows.
docs/dogfooding.md:5:Use `pnpm dogfood:rails` when changing the unified run rails or before release-like handoff. It first builds the local package bin, then runs a deterministic subset of RunForge's own checks through `runforge run --task command-check`:
docs/dogfooding.md:34:`code-proposal` remains gated even in dogfood. It emits `proposal.patch` and `patch-summary.md` as local artifacts, requires a human decision, and does not mutate the target repository by default.
docs/alpha-snapshot-2026-07-02.md:48:- RunForge requires a human decision before any proposed change is applied.
docs/alpha-snapshot-2026-07-02.md:54:- It does not perform semantic rewriting or broad multi-file planning.
